cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and specifically on face frontalization, which is a common problem in face recognition. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a novel Dual-Attention Generative Adversarial Network (DA-GAN) for face frontalization, which involves training a generator and discriminator using deep learning techniques. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (machine learning), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), and cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing). Finally, the paper includes experiments and results that involve image processing and analysis, which could also make it relevant to sub-category cs.MM (multimedia).
